JOHANNESBURG – President Jacob Zuma on Saturday unveiled a road and bridge in honour of the late African National Congress (ANC) struggle stalwart Dumisani Makhaye. The president unveiled the over R1 billion project at the Sugar Ray Xulu Stadium in Durban. Makhaye was a former MEC in the KwaZulu-Natal government. The project is the country’s biggest road infrastructure development in the last five years. “We used world-class engineering experts for the construction of this road. The engineering techniques applied in the construction of this road, has been recognised by the SA Institute of civil engineering and consulting engineers of South Africa," said Zuma.  eNCA